A MAN has been arrested in connection with the death of a woman at a flat in Glasgow.
The body of Anna Rosenberg, 43, was discovered at a property in Maryhill on Sunday.
Police sealed off the nine-storey block on Carrbridge Drive at around 4.20pm and carried out door-to-door enquiries in the area.
Police Scotland today confirmed that a 50-year-old man had been arrested and is detained in police custody in connection with the death.
A spokeswoman said: &quot;Relatives are aware.&quot;A report will be submitted to the procurator fiscal.&quot;
